# Burst ingest profile — Phase 5
#
# Holds at a quiet baseline (20 req/s) for 1 minute to warm up, then spikes
# to 200 req/s for 30 seconds (the burst), holds at 200 for another 30 seconds,
# then recovers back to 20 req/s over 30 seconds and holds for 2 minutes.
#
# Use this to observe:
#   - Whether the Capture Proxy recovers gracefully after a burst (no crash, no
#     stuck connections, error rate returns to baseline after burst ends)
#   - Kafka lag accumulation during the spike and how fast it drains afterwards
#   - k6 "dropped_iterations" counter — if VUs can't keep up with 200 req/s,
#     iterations are dropped and logged in the k6 terminal summary
#
# NOTE: error rate and p95 latency thresholds WILL likely breach during the
# 200 req/s spike (that is the point — proxy saturation is the expected finding).
# k6 will exit non-zero. Use Grafana to inspect the time-series behaviour rather
# than relying on the exit code for pass/fail.
#
# Total test duration: 4 minutes 30 seconds.

CAPTURE_PROXY_URL=https://capture-proxy:9200
INDEX_NAME=nyc_taxis
EXECUTOR=ramping-arrival-rate
RAMP_STAGES=[{"duration":"1m","target":20},{"duration":"30s","target":200},{"duration":"30s","target":200},{"duration":"30s","target":20},{"duration":"2m","target":20}]

INGEST_VUS=60
INGEST_MAX_VUS=250

BULK_BATCH_SIZE=20
SEQUENCE_FRACTION=0.15
CONNECTION_MODE=pinned
